<Layout
	title="Contact & Incident Submission"
	meta_title="Submit Forensic Telemetry | ErrorLedger"
	description="Submit technical root cause analysis files, forensic telemetry logs, or request post-mortem investigations from the ErrorLedger team."
	pubDate={new Date('July 15, 2026')}
	tags={["meta", "contact", "submissions"]}
>
	<h2>Incident Data Ingestion Portal</h2>
	<p>
		ErrorLedger functions as an independent technical reference. If you are a systems engineer, security researcher, or network administrator with validated post-mortem telemetry, we accept technical submissions.
	</p>

	<h3>Sourcing Verification Standard</h3>
	<p>
		To maintain database integrity, all external submissions must provide verifiable references to original datasets. This includes cryptographic transaction proofs, network routing table logs, or official security disclosure chains.
	</p>

	<h3>Submit a Record for Investigation</h3>
	<p>
		To propose a system failure for forensic analysis, or to submit verified telemetry, contact our registry operations team directly:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Secure Intake Node:</strong> intake@errorledger.com</li>
		<li><strong>Public Directory Queries:</strong> contact@errorledger.com</li>
	</ul>
</Layout>